About

How we started

In 2015, at Samskar School in Moti Nagar, a young martial artist with nothing but passion and a dream began teaching Taekwondo. That martial artist was Saganamonu Narendar. With just one student, he started a journey that would grow far beyond what he imagined.

Coach Narendar believed Taekwondo was more than kicks, punches, or medals — it was a way to build confidence, discipline, and inner strength. With that belief, he poured his heart into training, one class at a time. Word spread, students came, and what began as a humble practice quickly transformed into Doyen Taekwondo Academy — a place where over 1,000 students have since discovered their own strength.

Today, Doyen is more than an academy — it’s a community. Children learn focus and discipline, teens discover self-confidence, adults find fitness and resilience, and women are empowered with the skills and courage to protect themselves. Every student steps onto the mat not just to train, but to grow — in strength, in spirit, and in character.

What sets us apart is simple: while many academies are built for business, Doyen was built for purpose. Under the guidance of Coach Narendar — a certified Black Belt Dan-2 holder, national medalist, and licensed instructor — every student receives not just instruction, but mentorship. At Doyen Taekwondo Academy, martial arts is not about never losing — it’s about never backing down.

This is our story. And we’re here to help you write yours.
